  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# 🌿 Cashew Disease Prediction - Neural Engine Training\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook handles the end-to-end training pipeline for the Cashew Disease Detection platform. It downloads the dataset from Google Drive, trains a MobileNetV3 model, and exports it to ONNX for production use.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 🚀 Submission Checklist:\n",
        "1.  **Dataset Acquisition**: Direct from Google Drive via File ID.\n",
        "2.  **Architecture**: Optimized MobileNetV3 Small (Micro-AI).\n",
        "3.  **Export Path**: `models/cashew_micro.onnx` (for Unified Neural Engine).\n",
        "4.  **Forensic Meta**: Generates class mappings for diagnostic reporting."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 📥 1. Dataset Acquisition (Google Drive)\n",
        "Replace `YOUR_DRIVE_FILE_ID_HERE` with your file's share ID from Drive."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# --- GOOGLE DRIVE DATASET DOWNLOAD ---\n",
        "%pip install gdown\n",
        "\n",
        "import gdown\n",
        "import zipfile\n",
        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Paste your Google Drive File ID here\n",
        "# (Make sure the file is set to 'Anyone with the link' on Drive)\n",
        "drive_file_id = 'YOUR_DRIVE_FILE_ID_HERE'\n",
        "output_zip = 'cashewdataset.zip'\n",
        "\n",
        "if not os.path.exists('dataset'):\n",
        "    print(\"📂 Downloading dataset from Google Drive...\")\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        url = f'https://drive.google.com/uc?id={drive_file_id}'\n",
        "        gdown.download(url, output_zip, quiet=False)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        print(\"📦 Extracting files...\")\n",
        "        with zipfile.ZipFile(output_zip, 'r') as zip_ref:\n",
        "            zip_ref.extractall('.')\n",
        "        \n",
        "        # Handle directory naming (Rename extracted folder to 'dataset')\n",
        "        extracted_dirs = [d for d in os.listdir('.') if os.path.isdir(d) and 'cashew' in d.lower()]\n",
        "        if extracted_dirs:\n",
        "            os.rename(extracted_dirs[0], 'dataset')\n",
        "            print(f\"✅ Renamed {extracted_dirs[0]} to 'dataset'\")\n",
        "            \n",
        "        print(\"✅ Dataset preparation complete!\")\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"❌ ERROR: {e}\")\n",
        "        print(\"TIP: Ensure your Drive file is PUBLIC (Anyone with link).\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"📂 'dataset' folder already exists. Skipping download.\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## ⚙️ 2. Environment Setup & Core Logic"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%pip install torch torchvision onnx onnxruntime opencv-python matplotlib\n",
        "\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "import torch.nn as nn\n",
        "import torch.optim as optim\n",
        "from torchvision import datasets, transforms, models\n",
        "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader\n",
        "import json\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Constants\n",
        "IMG_SIZE = 224\n",
        "BATCH_SIZE = 16\n",
        "DEVICE = \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\"\n",
        "print(f\"[*] Using Device: {DEVICE}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 🧪 3. Data Processing & Augmentation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "transform = transforms.Compose([\n",
        "    transforms.Resize((IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE)),\n",
        "    transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(),\n",
        "    transforms.RandomRotation(15),\n",
        "    transforms.ToTensor(),\n",
        "    transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225])\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "if os.path.exists('dataset'):\n",
        "    full_dataset = datasets.ImageFolder('dataset', transform=transform)\n",
        "    train_size = int(0.8 * len(full_dataset))\n",
        "    val_size = len(full_dataset) - train_size\n",
        "    train_set, val_set = torch.utils.data.random_split(full_dataset, [train_size, val_size])\n",
        "\n",
        "    train_loader = DataLoader(train_set, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)\n",
        "    val_loader = DataLoader(val_set, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    class_names = full_dataset.classes\n",
        "    print(f\"✅ Classes detected: {class_names}\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"❌ ERROR: 'dataset' folder not found. Run Step 1 first.\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 🧠 4. Model Architecture & Training"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Load MobileNetV3 Small (Optimized for Micro-AI Platform)\n",
        "model = models.mobilenet_v3_small(weights='IMAGENET1K_V1')\n",
        "model.classifier[3] = nn.Linear(model.classifier[3].in_features, len(class_names))\n",
        "model = model.to(DEVICE)\n",
        "\n",
        "criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
        "optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"🚀 Starting Training Loop...\")\n",
        "epochs = 10\n",
        "for epoch in range(epochs):\n",
        "    model.train()\n",
        "    running_loss = 0.0\n",
        "    for inputs, labels in train_loader:\n",
        "        inputs, labels = inputs.to(DEVICE), labels.to(DEVICE)\n",
        "        optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
        "        outputs = model(inputs)\n",
        "        loss = criterion(outputs, labels)\n",
        "        loss.backward()\n",
        "        optimizer.step()\n",
        "        running_loss += loss.item()\n",
        "    \n",
        "    print(f\"Epoch [{epoch+1}/{epochs}] - Loss: {running_loss/len(train_loader):.4f}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 📦 5. Model Export (ONNX Format)\n",
        "This is the version used for high-performance production inference."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "os.makedirs('models', exist_ok=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Save PyTorch State Dict\n",
        "torch.save(model.state_dict(), 'models/cashew_micro_pt.pth')\n",
        "print(\"✅ PyTorch Model Saved: models/cashew_micro_pt.pth\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Export to ONNX\n",
        "model.eval()\n",
        "dummy_input = torch.randn(1, 3, 224, 224).to(DEVICE)\n",
        "\n",
        "torch.onnx.export(\n",
        "    model, \n",
        "    dummy_input, \n",
        "    \"models/cashew_micro.onnx\",\n",
        "    export_params=True,\n",
        "    opset_version=14,\n",
        "    do_constant_folding=True,\n",
        "    input_names=['input'],\n",
        "    output_names=['output'],\n",
        "    dynamic_axes={'input': {0: 'batch_size'}, 'output': {0: 'batch_size'}}\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✅ ONNX Model Exported: models/cashew_micro.onnx\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## ✅ Final Verification\n",
        "Verify that the model loads in ONNX Runtime."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import onnxruntime as ort\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    session = ort.InferenceSession(\"models/cashew_micro.onnx\")\n",
        "    print(\"🔥 ONNX Engine Verification: SUCCESS\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Model Inputs: {[i.name for i in session.get_inputs()]}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Model Outputs: {[o.name for o in session.get_outputs()]}\")\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"❌ ERROR: {e}\")"
      ]
    }
